
Installing Mondrian:

The easiest way to install is to run:  sudo ./install

Otherwise, the program (mondrian) needs to be placed in a directory that is
on your execution path.  /usr/bin or ~/bin are usually good choices.  Copy
the libraries in lib/ to a directory on your LD_LIBRARY_PATH.


Running Mondrian:

If the program crashes or if you find other bugs, please check the web page
first to see if they have already been reported.

On OS X, this program requires XQuartz, the X11 server.  Before running
this program, you must first start XQuartz.


Notes on Mondrian:



The main Web page for Mondrian is

    http://www.newplanetsoftware.com/

